title: PPPP’s Faqir Sher Muhammmad wins PS- 54 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Fakir Sher Muhammad has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-54, Tharparkar-III, by securing 69,088 votes.
According to the unofficial results issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Arbab Togachi Fawad of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged votes 34,413.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 68.54 %.
